OL,3,CTop doctor raising awareness of
OL,4,C'gentle' caesareans to improve
OL,5,Cchildbirth
OL,7,F"It's not much to ask and we all know
OL,8,Fthe benefits. We all know how
OL,9,Fimportant skin-to-skin is; to keep the
OL,10,Fbaby warm and improve the bonding with
OL,11,Fthe mum, and also how important the
OL,12,Fdelayed cord clamping is to give the
OL,13,Fbaby oxygen and iron.
OL,15,F"There's no rush in doing these things
OL,16,Fand there shouldn't be unless there is
OL,17,Fa reason. If the baby needs to go and
OL,18,Fget checked, of course we're going to
OL,19,Fdo that, but in most planned caesarean
OL,20,Fbirths and a lot of unplanned ones as
OL,21,Fwell, the baby is absolutely fine.
